Using Preformatted Text

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="UTF-8" />

<title>Preformatted text</title>

</head>

<body>

<p>Add this to your style sheet if you want to display a dotted border
underneath the <code>abbr</code> element

whenever it has a <code>title</code> attribute.</p>

<pre>

<code>

abbr[title] {

border-bottom: 1px dotted #000;

}

</code>

</pre>

</body>

</html>

