Offering Alternate Text

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Barcelona's Market</title>

</head>

<body>

<h2>Barcelona's Market</h2>

<img src="cornermrket.jpg" alt="Fruit Stand in Market" />

<p>This first picture shows one of the fruit stands in the Mercat de la
Boquería, the central market that is just

off the Rambles. It's an incredible place, full of every kind of fruit,
meat, fish, or whatever you might happen

to need. It took me a long time to get up the nerve to actually take a
picture there. You might say I'm kind of

a chicken, but since I lived there, it was just sort of strange. Do you
take pictures of your supermarket?</p>

<p><em>Note to Readers:</em> The alternate text shows only if the image
doesn't load. If you want to see how the

alternate text appears in a browser, change the image file name
referenced in the HTML of this page from

<code>src="cornermarket.jpg"</code> to an image that doesn't exist in
the folder, such as

<code>src="market.jpg"</code>.</p>

</body>

</html>

