Chapter 17 Video, Audio, and Other Multimedia

Adding a Single Video to Your Web Page

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>WebM Video</title>

</head>

<body>

<h1>WebM Video</h1>

<video src="paddle-steamer.webm"></video>

</body>

</html>

Output

[[file:media/image99.png]]

Adding Controls and Autoplay to Your Video

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>WebM Video with Controls</title>

</head>

<body>

<h1>WebM Video with Controls</h1>

<video src="paddle-steamer.webm" controls="controls"></video>

</body>

</html>

Output

[[file:media/image100.png]]

Looping a Video and Specifying a Poster Image

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>WebM Video with Autoplay and Loop</title>

</head>

<body>

<h1>WebM Video with Autoplay and Loop</h1>

<video src="paddle-steamer.webm" autoplay="autoplay"
loop="loop"></video>

</body>

</html>

Output

[[file:media/image101.png]]

Preventing a Video from Preloading

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>WebM Video with Preload:None</title>

</head>

<body>

<h1>WebM Video with Preload:None</h1>

<video src="paddle-steamer.webm" preload="none"
controls="controls"></video>

</body>

</html>

Output

[[file:media/image102.png]]

Using Video with Multiple Sources

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Video with Sources and Message Fallback</title>

</head>

<body>

<h1>Video with Sources and Message Fallback</h1>

<video controls="controls">

<source src="paddle-steamer.mp4" type="video/mp4">

<source src="paddle-steamer.webm" type="video/webm">

<p>Sorry, your browser doesn't support the <code>video</code>
element</p>

</video>

</body>

</html>

Output

[[file:media/image103.png]]

Adding Video with Hyperlink Fallbacks

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Video with Sources and Hyperlink Fallback</title>

</head>

<body>

<h1>Video with Sources and Hyperlink Fallback</h1>

<video controls="controls">

<source src="paddle-steamer.mp4" type="video/mp4">

<source src="paddle-steamer.webm" type="video/webm">

<a href="paddle-steamer.mp4">Download the video</a>

</video>

</body>

</html>

Output

[[file:media/image104.png]]

Adding Video with Flash Fallbacks

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Video with Sources and Flash Fallback</title>

</head>

<body>

<h1>Video with Sources and Flash Fallback</h1>

<video controls="controls">

<source src="paddle-steamer.mp4" type="video/mp4">

<source src="paddle-steamer.webm" type="video/webm">

<object type="application/x-shockwave-flash"
data="player.swf?videoUrl=paddle-steamer.mp4&controls=true">

<param name="movie"
value="player.swf?videoUrl=paddle-steamer.mp4&controls=true" />

</object>

</video>

<!-- NOTE: The Flash video player (player.swf) is JW Player from
http://www.longtailvideo.com/players/jw-flv-player. -->

</body>

</html>

Output

[[file:media/image105.png]]

