[[file:media/image116.png]]

Chapter 19 Working with Scripts

Loading an External Script

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Loading an External Script</title>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/base.css" />

</head>

<body>

<p>... All of your HTML content is here ...</p>

<p>See the HTML code and comments regarding how to load external
JavaScript files directly before the

<code>&lt;/body&gt;</code> end tag.</p>

<!-- Typically, for best performance results, load your JavaScript at
the very end of your page, right before the end </body> tag as shown
below in this page.

I recommend placing your JavaScript files in a sub-directory much like
you should with your CSS files. For example, some people create a folder
called "js" or "scripts" to house their JavaScript. If you do that, be
sure to change the file path in the src attribute. For example, change
it to src="js/behavior.js" if the file lives in a folder named "js," as
demonstrated in load-before-body-end-tag-example2.html. -->

<script src="behavior.js"></script>

<body>

</html>

Adding an Embedded Script

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Adding an Embedded Script</title>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/base.css" />

</head>

<body>

<p>... All of your HTML content is here ...</p>

<p>See the HTML code regarding how to embed JavaScript directly before
the <code>&lt;/body&gt;</code> end tag.</p>

<!-- See related comments in load-before-body-end-tag.html and
load-in-head.html. -->

<script>

/*

Your JavaScript code goes here

*/

</script>

<body>

</html>

Chapter 20 Testing & Debugging Web Pages

Checking the Easy Stuff: HTML

Code

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Malformed start tag</title>

</head>

<body>

<p>We've <fm>really</em> got a problem here.</p>

</body>

</html>

Output

[[file:media/image117.png]]

Validating Your Code

Code

Error

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Mary Anna, the Iguana</title>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/base.css" />

</head>

<body>

<h1>Mary Anna, the Iguana<h1>

<img src="img/iguana.jpg" width="220" height="165" alt="Mary Anna, the
Iguana" />

<p>There once was an iguana<br />

whose name was Mary Anna<br />

her skin was so dry<br />

that she'd have to cry<br />

Here's some cream: would you please put it onna?</p>

</body>

</html>

Fixed

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Mary Anna, the Iguana</title>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/base.css" />

</head>

<body>

<h1>Mary Anna, the Iguana</h1>

<img src="img/iguana.jpg" width="220" height="165" alt="Mary Anna, the
Iguana" />

<p>There once was an iguana<br />

whose name was Mary Anna<br />

her skin was so dry<br />

that she'd have to cry<br />

Here's some cream: would you please put it onna?</p>

</body>

</html>

Output

Error

[[file:media/image118.png]]

Fixed

[[file:media/image119.png]]

Testing Your Page

Code

Error

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Mary Anna, the Iguana</title>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css" />

</head>

<body>

<h1>Mary Anna, the Iguana</h1>

<p><img src="img/iguana.jpg" width="220" height="165" alt="Mary Anna,
the Iguana" />

There once was an iguana<br />

whose name was Mary Anna<br />

her skin was so dry<br />

that she'd have to cry<br />

Here's some cream:<br />

would you please put it onna?</p>

</body>

</html>

Fixed

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="utf-8" />

<title>Mary Anna, the Iguana</title>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/styles.css" />

</head>

<body>

<h1>Mary Anna, the Iguana</h1>

<p><img src="img/iguana.jpg" width="220" height="165" alt="Mary Anna,
the Iguana" />

There once was an iguana<br />

whose name was Mary Anna<br />

her skin was so dry<br />

that she'd have to cry<br />

